Bulgaria,[a] officially the Republic of Bulgaria,[b] is a country
in Southeast Europe. It is situated on the eastern portion of the Balkans
directly south of the Danube river and west of the Black Sea. Bulgaria
is bordered by Greece and Turkey to the south, Serbia and North Macedonia
to the west, and Romania to the north. It covers a territory of 110,994
square kilometres (42,855 sq mi) and is the sixteenth-largest country
in Europe by area and the tenth largest within the European Union.
